Movie: Feet in Water, Head on Fire

Review: That was nice that Chihiro still wanted to be No Face's friend after he ate some people because she knew he really didn't mean it.

I loved that the characters of this film lived in the gray area, mirroring so much of how we understand our interactions with the natural world and technological progress. My mouth was open in wonder for most of the film because of how beautiful the animation was. This one has more danger than the other Ghiblis that I have watched, which have not been many.
Whenever I am down, I will sing the Totoro song and imagine I am riding on the catbus. Might be the best kids movie I've ever seen.
